Package: TwoTankModel
Title: Two-Tank Conceptual Rainfall-Runoff Model with Monte Carlo Calibration
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Madan", "Pokhrel",
                  email = "madnapokhrel83@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut","cre"))
Description: A user-friendly two-tank linear-reservoir conceptual
    rainfall-runoff model for daily streamflow simulation. Upper tank
    represents surface runoff and interflow; lower tank represents
    baseflow. Includes Monte Carlo calibration with Latin Hypercube
    Sampling, prediction uncertainty envelopes, parameter identifiability
    diagnostics, and publication-ready plots. Designed for comparative
    watershed analysis under identical precipitation forcing.
